      {
        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "**Summary verdict:** EDTA is an outstanding chelator. With log β values ranging from ~7.4 (UO₂²⁺) to ~27.8 (Bi³⁺), it forms stable 1:1 complexes with virtually every metal in the periodic table. Higher-charged metals (Fe³⁺, V³⁺, Bi³⁺) bind with extraordinary affinity (log β > 25), while even \"weak\" targets like Ca²⁺ (log β = 10.7) are firmly sequestered under physiological conditions. Its hexadentate structure, broad metal scope, and 596 measured stability constants in SRD-46 confirm EDTA as the gold-standard chelating agent in analytical chemistry, medicine, and industry.",
